    m_RichText: 1
    m_HorizontalOverflow: 0
    m_VerticalOverflow: 0
    m_LineSpacing: 1
  m_Text: "Extendable enums are an easy way to create enums and add to enumerators
    without having to go into the code, allowing designers to create new behaviours
    on the fly if that behaviour is determined by an enum. EnumExample is a data
    asset with an enum value but is also the method of which you can extend the enum,
    by using the inspector dropdown on it's value field. Credits to Cory Koseck\r
    for making the excellent ExtendEnum base used for this implementation."
